**Abstract (paste inside Word file):**

> The AI Public Health Chatbot for Disease Awareness is designed to provide users with
 basic health guidance through an interactive chat-based system. The chatbot collects symptoms
  from users and predicts possible health conditions using Machine Learning models for tabular data,
   Deep Learning CNN models for medical images, and Soft Computing techniques for handling uncertainty in diseases such as asthma.
    A closed-domain language model is used to generate user-friendly explanations while ensuring medical safety. 
    The system aims to improve public health awareness, enable early risk identification, and reduce unnecessary hospital visits.
     This solution is lightweight, cost-effective, and suitable for real-world deployment.
